    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1897</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Jane 18.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 372.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Relating to my dispatch No. 337, of April 30
                    last, I have the honor to inform you that as no reply has been received from the
                    German foreign office to my note of that date, in the case of Alfred Meyer, I
                    have again invited Baron von Marschall’s attention to the case and have
                    requested that an early disposition of it may be made, and that the speedy
                    release may be ordered of this native-born American citizen, who has already
                    been held to involuntary service in the German army for more than eight
                    months.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin P. Uhl.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
